.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
\fBPackFile\fP is a class with two purposes\&. First, it implements \fBIFileLoader\fP, allowing to be used as a simple file system\&. Second, it has the Pack and Unpack methods, used to create \&.pak files, used by this file system\&. Creating \&.pak files has several benefits\&. The first one is obfuscation, making it more difficult to end users to get access to your game assets\&. The second one is being loaded as a stream, as it allows to only load what is needed at the moment\&. It also is easily extended to, for example, zip all or only specific files, reducing final build size\&. Ownership: 


.IP "\(bu" 2
It takes ownership of the point in memory where the pak file is\&. However, it is created as a stream and not loaded fully on initialization\&. Guarantees:
.IP "\(bu" 2
If the file exist at the specified path and is a valid pak file, the metadata will be loaded and the pack open\&. Thread safe:
.IP "\(bu" 2
GetFile is not thread safe, as it uses a single handler to seek and read data\&. Check \fBIFileLoader\&.h\fP for more info on the interface methods\&. 
.PP

